</note>
</section>
<section id="sect-00010">
<title>Toremifene</title>
<para id="para-00021">Toremifene is used to treat clients who have estrogen receptor-positive advanced breast cancer. Toremifene works by binding to estrogen receptors, which prevents cancer cells from developing. Contraindications include allergy to the drug, pregnancy and lactation, and hypercalcemia. Caution must be used in prescribing toremifene to clients with renal or hepatic dysfunction or bone marrow suppression. Adverse effects are like menopausal symptoms, which were discussed in <emphasis effect="bold"><link document="m00477">Review of the Female Reproductive System</link></emphasis>.</para>
