<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>estrogen receptor modulators (ERMs)</term> <meaning>nonhormone drugs that stimulate or block estrogen receptor sites; used to treat osteoporosis in postmenopause</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>osteopenia</term> <meaning>the condition in which bone is losing density</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>osteoporosis</term> <meaning>the condition when bone loss is significant and bone has become porous and brittle</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
